1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,720
I'd like to ask the question this morning about who are you?

2
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:07,960
If you remember, a rock group, The Who, sang a song like that.

3
00:00:08,020 --> 00:00:12,510
They asked, who are you? To whom do you belong?

4
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:18,840
The reason I ask that question is because in this worship series, we're coming towards the end.

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:26,280
We're getting at who we are as a people who worship, and your identity of who you are shapes your behavior.

6
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:30,580
Who you are shapes what you do.

7
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:34,980
Now, how many of you have seen the film Toy Story?

8
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:38,500
All right, a very sophisticated congregation.

9
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:39,740
I think that's exciting.

10
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:44,040
If you did not see the film, it's a great children's film,

11
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,840
but it's really a film about adult themes as well.

12
00:00:47,460 --> 00:00:50,740
It's about toys, but it's really about identity.

13
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,260
Who are we?

14
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:56,460
And if we know who we are, then it changes our behavior.

15
00:00:57,020 --> 00:01:01,800
I'd like for you to see this scene where Buzz and Woody learn

16
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,860
what it means to be who they are

17
00:01:03,860 --> 00:01:05,440
and how that affects their lives.

18
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:06,000
Take a look.

19
00:01:37,650 --> 00:01:40,470
...nation, God's own people,

20
00:01:40,830 --> 00:01:42,770
in order that you might proclaim

21
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,530
the mighty acts of Him

22
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:46,230
who called you out of darkness

23
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:48,470
into His marvelous light.

24
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:51,410
Once you were not a people,

25
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,420
but now you are God's people.

26
00:01:55,530 --> 00:01:57,270
Once you had not received mercy,

27
00:01:57,710 --> 00:02:00,350
but now you have received mercy.

28
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,780
Your identity shapes your behavior.

29
00:02:04,180 --> 00:02:07,370
Who you are shapes what you do.

30
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:14,910
Church, on the bottom of your feet, it says God.

31
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,800
He owns you.

32
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:21,400
You have a purpose and identity.

33
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,640
And never forget it.

34
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,220
Never forget whose you are.

35
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:28,980
We're in a worship series.

36
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:32,120
We're wrestling with what it means to be a church that worships God.

37
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:35,680
We've begun to see that as we come together that God is the audience,

38
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:41,140
that we are the participants, the worship leaders here are the prompters in this experience

39
00:02:41,140 --> 00:02:43,300
of giving ourselves to God.

40
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:49,600
And knowing who we are will dictate what we do in worship.

41
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:55,070
Knowing who we are will affect what we bring unto God.

42
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,630
Now God asks that we give our entire selves to Him.

43
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:02,570
He asks that we give our bodies to Him.

44
00:03:02,570 --> 00:03:09,200
He asks that we give our souls and our will and our emotions and everything unto Him.

45
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:12,930
In Romans 12, beginning 1 and 2,

46
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:19,430
And so, dear brothers and sisters, I plead with you to give your bodies to God.

47
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:24,940
Let them be a living and a holy sacrifice, the kind that He will accept.

48
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:30,140
When you think of what He has done for you, is this too much to ask?

49
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:33,880
Don't copy the behaviors and customs of the world.

50
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:40,440
but let God transform you into a new person by changing the way you think.

51
00:03:41,850 --> 00:03:43,990
Then you will know what God wants you to do,

52
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:48,890
and you will know how good and pleasing His perfect will really is.

53
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:53,680
To give our bodies and our minds unto God as an act of worship,

54
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:56,340
we need to know who we are.

55
00:03:57,340 --> 00:03:58,800
And Peter makes it clear.

56
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,640
We are a chosen people.

57
00:04:03,370 --> 00:04:04,590
You believe that, church?

58
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:06,430
You're a chosen people.

59
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,920
This is not just intellectual fodder for thought over lunch.

60
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:14,340
This is life-changing stuff.

61
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:16,810
Are you ready to hear this?

62
00:04:18,410 --> 00:04:19,450
It's a good time for an amen.

63
00:04:20,170 --> 00:04:21,350
Are you ready to hear this?

64
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:22,670
All right.

65
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:24,750
You're a chosen people.

66
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:28,970
God has chosen us, and he wants us to respond to him.

67
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:35,310
Jesus Christ has offered to us a new and an intimate relationship with God himself.

68
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:40,880
And we're not chosen to do as we like, we're chosen to do as God likes.

69
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,480
We're chosen to serve.

70
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:49,680
We're chosen to bless Him and honor Him in who we are and what we do.

71
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:54,280
You're a chosen people and you're a royal priesthood.

72
00:04:55,590 --> 00:04:56,490
Now what's a priest?

73
00:04:56,850 --> 00:05:04,300
A priest is someone who has access to God and helps others make that connection.

74
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:09,870
A priest functions, as one has termed it, as a bridge builder.

75
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:14,380
One who builds the bridge between God and somebody else.

76
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:20,560
Friends, you are a royal priesthood because through Jesus Christ, the great high priest,

77
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:28,520
we have access to God and we're challenged and charged to help others find him as well.

78
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,520
What a huge calling on our lives.

79
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:39,920
Bridge builders to God to help others connect with Jesus that they might find the Father.

80
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,780
It's a great responsibility.

81
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:50,200
If you're struggling with purpose in life, friends, you are to be bridge builders to God

82
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,500
of the people that are lost around you.

83
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,280
What a holy calling.

84
00:05:55,700 --> 00:06:01,880
You're a holy nation, says Peter, set apart because God lives in us

85
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:08,560
And through the Holy Spirit, we are set apart to accomplish God's purposes in the world.

86
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,480
You're a holy nation.

87
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,640
We're a people for God to specially possess.

88
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:17,480
Now why is that important?

89
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:22,260
Well, when God possesses us, as we've seen in this film, as we see in other places,

90
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:28,080
the value of something is often determined by whether someone has possessed it or not.

91
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:32,370
I've been to that restaurant, Planet Hollywood.

92
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:34,050
Some of you may have never been there.

93
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:42,110
essentially a big glorified burger joint with lots of artifacts from movies throughout the restaurant.

94
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:47,730
And behind glass you'll find pieces of costume worn in various films.

95
00:06:48,730 --> 00:06:54,350
And if you get up close, you'll notice that much of what you see is common ordinary clothing,

96
00:06:54,870 --> 00:07:02,860
but because Schwarzenegger wore it, or Madonna put it on, or Rob Lowe used that in such and such scene,

97
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,360
It's of great value.

98
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:07,420
Thousands of dollars for a pair of shoes.

99
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:14,060
One place I saw the shoes that were used by Forrest Gump.

100
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:18,870
They're just a pair of Nike, 60 bucks down at the shoe store.

101
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:23,680
But because Forrest wore them in the film, they're priceless.

102
00:07:25,230 --> 00:07:25,570
Almost.

103
00:07:28,180 --> 00:07:30,480
Who owns them gives them the value.

104
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:35,760
Who owns you gives you your value.

105
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:41,040
and you're a holy nation, a priesthood unto God.

106
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:46,350
In the film, they're Andy's toys.

107
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:49,450
They're not just toys off the shelf.

108
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:52,490
They're not just one of a million plastic parts

109
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:53,530
sent around the world.

110
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:55,670
They belong to Andy.

111
00:07:55,670 --> 00:07:58,650
And because they belong to Andy, they have value.

112
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:01,570
You may feel beat up in life.

113
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:03,470
You may feel like you're insignificant.

114
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:06,790
You're just one more drone walking through the world.

115
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:17,030
But friends, if you know Jesus Christ and the Spirit is in you, you are God's holy nation, royal priesthood, king's kids, and never forget it.

116
00:08:18,050 --> 00:08:18,310
Amen?

117
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:24,490
You have value because you're owned and bought by the king.

118
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:28,110
And never let anybody take that away.

119
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:30,900
You're stamped on your feet.

120
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:34,740
You're stamped on your soul by God himself.

121
00:08:40,430 --> 00:08:46,110
God calls us to be a holy people, a priesthood, to worship and praise.

122
00:08:46,110 --> 00:08:47,970
In the words of Peter, why?

123
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:51,230
To declare God's mighty acts.

124
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,550
Declare his acts.

125
00:08:56,220 --> 00:09:00,540
One of the ways we get to know somebody is by what they've done.

126
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:05,160
A person's character is reflected in what they consistently do.

127
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:09,380
You get to know each other by seeing the track record of their life.

128
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,340
We often do that in a resume.

129
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,060
We see what they've done.

130
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,100
We see where they've been.

131
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,380
We see the kinds of things that a person does.

132
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,220
What would be on God's resume?

133
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:29,820
Would it just be big words, omniscient, all-knowing, all-seeing?

134
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,260
Those are big, heady phrases.

135
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:37,140
Or would it be also a list of the great actions of God?

136
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:46,830
And because of what he's done, we'd know who he is and his character by all the jobs he has done.

137
00:09:49,770 --> 00:09:52,310
Friends, God is not a philosophical proposition.

138
00:09:52,990 --> 00:10:00,570
God is not something on paper to wrestle with as some ethereal concept that makes the philosophers tingle.

139
00:10:00,950 --> 00:10:05,670
Friends, God is a being who acts in our space and our time.

140
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:08,170
He invades our very history.

141
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:17,480
And one of the ways that we worship this kind of God is to declare what he has done in the world.

142
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:24,220
The mighty acts of God as revealed in Scripture become the basis for our worship

143
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:31,340
as we declare what He has done page after page after page with God's people throughout the ages.

144
00:10:33,490 --> 00:10:40,730
And so the Scriptures become the basis for our worship life as we, in Peter's words, declare the mighty acts of God.

145
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:47,100
So number one, our faith as we learn about worship is based on God's acts in history.

146
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:51,450
Our faith is based on what He has done.

147
00:10:52,770 --> 00:10:56,630
You see, the Christian faith is event-centered.

148
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,380
It's event-centered.

149
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:03,900
It's based on things that have happened.

150
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:08,580
And there are three primary events we can point to this morning

151
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:11,420
that are pivotal for our understanding of who God is

152
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:14,180
and how we might declare His mighty acts.

153
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,480
The first one is the creation itself.

154
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:24,060
God is the creator of everything that you see and touch and smell and taste

155
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:27,100
and everything you can't in the spiritual realm as well.

156
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:31,650
God created the heavens and the earth.

157
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:37,300
And friends, the world we live in is no accident.

158
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,640
You are not an accident.

159
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:46,900
You're a holy nation created special by God for a purpose in life,

160
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,540
to honor him and to declare his mighty acts.

161
00:11:51,890 --> 00:11:53,750
Because he created us in his image,

162
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:56,130
we have eternal value and we have purpose

163
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:58,210
and you are special to God

164
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,790
because you're created by God.

165
00:12:03,170 --> 00:12:05,350
And so our worship becomes a reflection

166
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:08,260
of that reality.

167
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:11,940
We express our deep and full expression of our love

168
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:14,500
to the one who created us

169
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,830
and how intimate that is.

170
00:12:19,210 --> 00:12:21,330
Creation, the first primary event.

171
00:12:21,330 --> 00:12:28,360
the secondary one as we spoke about a few weeks ago as well as the exodus as the israelites

172
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:37,150
delivered from the egyptians and they're formed into a new nation people taken from bondage and

173
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:43,380
slavery in egypt led into the desert where god's law and god's mercy would shape them

174
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:50,140
and form the basis for their lives and while he levels judgment on the egyptians

175
00:12:51,230 --> 00:12:55,010
God's people were instructed to take an animal and to slay it

176
00:12:55,010 --> 00:13:00,410
and put the blood of that sacrifice on the doorposts of the homes.

177
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:07,870
And from there, God's Spirit moved and passed over them,

178
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:14,840
and they were spared and delivered and marked by that experience as delivered by God.

179
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:21,110
And friends, it sets up the whole system where we are experiencing Jesus as the one,

180
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:23,630
and greatest of all sacrifices.

181
00:13:25,070 --> 00:13:25,390
Amen.

182
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,180
A third great event of Scripture

183
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:31,500
that defines our faith and our worship

184
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,280
is the Christ event itself.

185
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:38,120
The life, the death, and the resurrection

186
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,800
of our Lord Jesus Christ.

187
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,920
In Christ, you are new creations,

188
00:13:46,350 --> 00:13:50,350
brand new, stamped with God's imprint on you.

189
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,560
His work begins in us then

190
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:58,620
to reclaim the creation, to reclaim the whole world.

191
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:05,120
And he's using you and you and you and you and you and you and me and all of us

192
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,020
to accomplish that purpose.

193
00:14:11,070 --> 00:14:16,380
So friends, we come to worship, to relive those mighty acts of God,

194
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:20,000
the creation, the exodus, Jesus' life, death, and resurrection.

195
00:14:21,350 --> 00:14:23,210
Our faith is based on those events.

196
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:30,780
Number two, we relive those acts of God in worship.

197
00:14:32,850 --> 00:14:39,150
You see, declaring these mighty acts, as the Scripture says, is a way to remember them.

198
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,900
And remembering them is to relive them.

199
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:51,260
And we worship God through remembering these amazing experiences and forays of God into our time and into our space.

200
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:57,900
And Scripture gives us this record of these foundational mighty acts of God.

201
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:01,950
Creation, exodus, lives and times of Jesus.

202
00:15:01,950 --> 00:15:06,330
and the way the church remembers these things,

203
00:15:06,330 --> 00:15:10,570
the way the church comes back to relive and remember them

204
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:15,830
is through symbols and rituals and worship experiences

205
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:18,990
that bring us back to those mighty events

206
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,100
that elevate our worship.

207
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:26,550
And particularly we remember God's work in Christ.

208
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:30,520
And so in the early church and throughout the church

209
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,220
they had a Christian calendar that was formed

210
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:36,140
to help us to remember God's mighty acts.

211
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,880
Let me give you some examples of this.

212
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:42,320
Advent, the season we're about to enter into.

213
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:45,680
A preparing for the way of the coming of the Lord.

214
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:49,960
A preparation time of looking forward to the birth of Jesus.

215
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:52,340
And then, of course, Christmas.

216
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:58,660
It's not just about toys and prizes on a Christmas morning and presents.

217
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:02,100
It's about Jesus being born for the world.

218
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:06,280
and I love all the presents and the trees and the toys

219
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:09,400
but it's really about Jesus

220
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:11,120
coming to the world

221
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:14,660
and that will be the focus of our celebration this year

222
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:18,020
and then later we move into Palm Sunday

223
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:21,880
remembering the arrival of Jesus into Jerusalem

224
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:24,520
and the beginning of the Passion Week

225
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:26,880
and then we move to Maundy Thursday

226
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:31,110
remembering the Last Supper with the disciples

227
00:16:31,110 --> 00:16:37,130
the betrayal, the Garden of Gethsemane, and the arrest of Jesus.

228
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:44,770
And then we come to Good Friday, and the church remembers the death of Jesus on the cross.

229
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:48,370
But then we come back Sunday.

230
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:53,550
Then we come back Sunday morning, Easter, my favorite holiday of the year.

231
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:58,590
Why? Because it's about the resurrection and the hope of Jesus Christ,

232
00:16:58,790 --> 00:17:01,910
the greatest day in the history of the world.

233
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:06,140
and we make a big deal about Easter

234
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:10,530
because it's the basis of our hope in Christ.

235
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:14,860
But then we move

236
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:17,740
and we're going to remember Ascension this year.

237
00:17:18,970 --> 00:17:21,870
Why? Because Jesus then gives the marching orders

238
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:23,470
for the church.

239
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:27,370
He's leaving and the job is left to us

240
00:17:27,370 --> 00:17:31,010
and we remember that experience in that Sunday.

241
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:33,870
And then Pentecost comes shortly thereafter

242
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:39,050
And we remember the Holy Spirit coming with power that the mission might be accomplished.

243
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:41,770
Not in our strength, but in His.

244
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:50,160
And you see the church calendar helps us remember and connect with these mighty acts of God.

245
00:17:50,740 --> 00:17:56,360
And as we talked about last week or two, we talk about communion and baptism again as experiences

246
00:17:56,360 --> 00:18:01,620
